      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RITUALIZE (6) has the class to win and first-up it's just a matter of fitness. Won a Doomben Maiden on a heavy track two back on debut and he's trialled well for his return. Maps well and Ben Thompson's booking is a decent push for his readiness. JAGGERY (5) did a good job here first-up and has been kept up to the mark with a Deagon trial. Goes second-up and has plenty up his sleeve. Tumbles in weight this grade with a 2kg claim atop, and he should manage the ground.  KING SPIRIT (2) seeks the hat-trick off comfortable soft track wins at Rockhampton. Keeps the handy 3kg claim and the shorter sprint won't be an issue. A chance as well. RUBYDOO (7) resumes and her form is good enough to keep onside.",
